feature.string:
UsesThe plant is of some slight medicinal value in India [see
Wealth of India 10 1976 397
]. There its pickled fruits are used as a dye. Corner (1.c.) notes that a reddish-purple coloration is imparted to potash solution in which seeds have been steeped.

Turraea pubescens is the only true Turraea in Asia and is closely related to some of the East African species. A similar transoceanic distribution is seen in the allied Naregamia Wight & Arn. [see
Cheek Kew Bull. 45 1990 711
], which comprises one species in India and a very closely related one in Angola.

